## Executive Overview

The NEO HYDRAULIC MATRIX represents the second major structural intelligence subsystem within the PI220 aerospace ecosystem.

Following the establishment of STARFRAME SF-1, a new challenge emerged:

> How can structural loads be actively managed instead of merely endured?

The answer became the NEO HYDRAULIC MATRIX.

Unlike conventional hydraulic systems that primarily actuate control surfaces and landing gear, the NEO HYDRAULIC MATRIX functions as a distributed stabilization network embedded throughout the vehicle architecture.

Its purpose is to transform hydraulic pressure into a dynamic structural governance system capable of:

* Load balancing
* Vibration suppression
* Structural stiffness modulation
* Resonance management
* Emergency compensation
* Flight stability enhancement

The result is a structural framework that continuously adapts to changing operational conditions.

